oc:kn_738712d9 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When formulating power system NLP problems" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Work in per-unit internally for power system optimization but convert back to physical units for output and cost functions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Per-unit scaling improves numerical conditioning of the optimization, but cost functions may expect MW rather than per-unit values." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a5f2d6a4 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When parsing MATPOWER branch data for power flow constraints" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never assume MATPOWER tap=0 means zero impedance; it means tap ratio is 1.0 (no transformer effect)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This convention trips up many implementations and leads to division-by-zero or incorrect power flow equations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_af11dc47 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When solver returns infeasible status" ;
    oc:directiveContent "On infeasible result: check bound consistency, constraint signs, unit conversions (degrees vs radians), and shunt sign conventions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Most infeasibilities in power system NLP are caused by data handling errors rather than genuinely infeasible formulations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b30dbfc4 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When solving any nonconvex optimization problem" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always use multiple initializations for nonconvex NLP problems; try data-derived (clipped to bounds) and flat start (Vm=1.0, Va=0.0) strategies." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Interior-point solvers like IPOPT converge to local optima; different starting points can find different local solutions, and the best should be selected." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_baec7d70 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assembling lbx, ubx, lbg, ubg arrays" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Variable bounds and constraint bounds must match the stacking order of the decision variable vector created by ca.vertcat." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Mismatched ordering causes silently incorrect constraint enforcement, leading to wrong solutions or infeasibility." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_e23f777b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When tuning IPOPT solver options" ;
    oc:directiveContent "IPOPT with adaptive mu_strategy and tol=1e-7 provides good balance of speed and accuracy for nonconvex power system problems; increase max_iter beyond 2000 for hard problems." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Default IPOPT settings are conservative; the recommended settings reduce output noise and improve convergence on nonconvex landscapes." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_f1ae63c4 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When extracting and reporting solver solutions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not round optimization results below 6 decimal places; keep high precision in solution outputs." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Over-rounding introduces numerical errors that compound when solutions are used in downstream power flow or economic calculations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_ff41e3d4 a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When running solver multiple times" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Solver results are deterministic given same x0, bounds, and constraints, but different initializations yield different local optima." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Nonconvex problems have multiple local optima; reproducibility requires fixing the initialization seed." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

